Abraham Joseph, 35, a driver, who was accused of sexually assaulting his two stepdaughters, appeared at an Ikeja Chief Magistrates’ Court on Wednesday.
The victims are aged 9 and 12.
Christopher John , the Prosecuting Inspector said the defendant committed the offence on May 5, at noon, at his residence.
ALSO READ:Woman tells court about her  gang-rape ordeal in Lekki hotel
The case was reported to the police by the girls’ mother, John said.
The accused pleaded not guilty.
Chief Magistrate P. E. Nwaka admitted the defendant to N200, 000 bail with two sureties in the like sum and adjourned till June 13.




















